\[ (Y|X=x) \sim N(\alpha+\beta x, \sigma^2) \]

\[ y=\alpha+\beta x+ \varepsilon \text{, where } \varepsilon\sim N(0,\sigma^2) \]

\(n\) \(\underline{x}\) \(Y_i\) \(X_i (i=1,\cdots, n)\)

\[ \begin{equation} (Y_i|X_i=x_i) \sim \text{NID}(\alpha+\beta x, \sigma^2) \text{ where } i=1,\cdots,n \end{equation} (\#eq:NID) \]

\(\text{NID}\) (normally and independently distributed) \(X_i\) @ref(fig:age-wt) Analysis of hierarchical and other dependent data (Term 2)

@ref(eq:NID)

\[ \begin{equation} (Y_i|X_i=x_i) = \alpha + \beta x_i + \varepsilon_i, \text{ where } \varepsilon_i\sim \text{NID}(0,\sigma^2) \end{equation} (\#eq:NID1) \]

\[ \begin{equation} y_i = \alpha + \beta x_i + \varepsilon_i, \text{ where } \varepsilon_i\sim \text{NID}(0,\sigma^2) \end{equation} (\#eq:NID2) \]

residuals

@ref(eq:NID1) @ref(eq:NID2)

\[ \varepsilon_i = y_i - (\alpha + \beta x_i) \]

\(\varepsilon_i\) \(i\) () (random error) (true residual) \(\alpha+\beta x_i\) \(y_i\) \((\alpha, \beta)\) \((\hat\alpha, \hat\beta)\) \((\alpha, \beta)\)

estimation of parameters

\((\alpha, \beta, \sigma^2)\) \(Y_i, X_i, (i=1, \cdots, n)\) (inference) (ordinary least squares, OLS) \(\hat\alpha, \hat\beta\) \(\alpha, \beta\) \(i\) (estimated expectation):

\[ \hat{y}_i=\hat\alpha+\hat\beta x_i \]

\(i\) (observed or fitted or estimated residuals)

\[ \hat{\varepsilon}_i = y_i-\hat{y}_i=y_i-(\hat\alpha+\hat\beta x_i) \]

\(\alpha, \beta\)

\(\alpha, \beta\) minimize the sum of squared deviations from the fitted regression lineOLS (residual sum of squares, \(SS_{RES}\)) \(\hat\alpha, \hat\beta\)

\[ \begin{equation} SS_{RES} = \sum_{i=1}^n \hat{\varepsilon}^2_i = \sum_{i=1}^n (y_i-\hat\alpha-\hat\beta x_i)^2 \end{equation} (\#eq:ssres) \]

OLS \(\alpha, \beta\)

\[ \begin{equation} \hat\alpha=\bar{y}-\hat\beta\bar{x} (\#eq:hatalpha) \end{equation} \]

\[ \begin{equation} \hat\beta=\frac{\sum_{i=1}^n(x_i-\bar{x})(y_i-\bar{y})}{\sum_{i=1}^n(x_i-\bar{x})^2} (\#eq:hatbeta) \end{equation} \]

\(\bar{y}=\frac{\sum_{i=1}^ny_i}{n}, \bar{x}=\frac{\sum_{i=1}^nx_i}{n}\)

\(SS_{RES}\) \(\alpha\) @ref(eq:ssres) \(\hat\alpha\) \(0\)

\[ \begin{aligned} & \frac{\text{d}SS_{RES}}{\text{d}\hat\alpha} =\sum_{i=1}^n -2(y_i-\hat\alpha-\hat\beta x_i) = 0\\ & \text{Since } \sum_{i=1}^n(y_i) = n\bar{y}; \sum_{i=1}^n (x_i) =n\bar{x} \\ & \Rightarrow -n\bar{y}+n\hat\alpha+n\hat\beta\bar{x} = 0 \\ & \Rightarrow \hat\alpha = \bar{y}-\hat\beta\bar{x} \end{aligned} \]

\(SS_{RES}\) \(\beta\) @ref(eq:ssres) \(\hat\alpha\)

\[ \begin{equation} \begin{split} SS_{RES} &= \sum_{i=1}^n\hat\varepsilon_i^2=\sum_{i=1}^n(y_i-(\bar{y}-\hat\beta\bar{x})-\hat\beta x_i)^2\\ &= \sum_{i=1}^n((y_i-\bar{y})-\hat\beta(x_i-\bar{x}))^2 \\ \end{split} (\#eq:ssres-rearrange) \end{equation} \]

@ref(eq:ssres-rearrange)

\[ \begin{aligned} &\frac{\mathrm{d} SS_{RES}}{\mathrm{d} \hat\beta} = \sum_{i=1}^n -2(x_i-\bar{x})(y_i-\bar{y}) + 2\hat\beta(x_i-\bar{x})^2 = 0\\ & \Rightarrow \hat\beta\sum_{i=1}^n(x_i-\bar{x})^2 = \sum_{i=1}^n (x_i-\bar{x})(y_i-\bar{y}) \\ & \hat\beta=\frac{\sum_{i=1}^n(x_i-\bar{x})(y_i-\bar{y})}{\sum_{i=1}^n(x_i-\bar{x})^2} \end{aligned} \]

@ref(eq:hatalpha) @ref(eq:hatbeta) \(\alpha, \beta\) (MLE)

Estimation of the residual variance \((\sigma^2)\)

\[ \begin{equation} \hat\sigma^2=\sum_{i=1}^n \frac{\hat\varepsilon^2}{n} = \sum_{i=1}^n \frac{(y_i-\hat\alpha-\hat\beta x_i)^2}{n} \end{equation} (\#eq:sigma2wrong) \]

\(\sigma^2\) (MLE) @ref(eq:sigma2wrong) (Section @ref(samplevarbias))

\[ \begin{equation} \hat\sigma^2=\sum_{i=1}^n \frac{\hat\varepsilon^2}{n-2} = \sum_{i=1}^n \frac{(y_i-\hat\alpha-\hat\beta x_i)^2}{n-2} \end{equation} (\#eq:sigma2right) \]

@ref(eq:sigma2right) (Residual Mean Squares, RMS) \(\text{MS}_{RES}\) \(n-2\) \(\alpha, \beta\) ( 2)

Ordinary Least Squares Estimators and Inference

\(\alpha, \beta, \sigma^2\) @ref(eq:hatalpha) @ref(eq:hatbeta) @ref(eq:sigma2right)

  1. \(\bar{y}=\frac{\sum_{i=1}^n y_i}{n}\) \(y\)
  2. \(\bar{x}=\frac{\sum_{i=1}^n x_i}{n}\) \(x\)
  3. \(SS_{yy}=\sum_{i=1}^n(y_i-\bar{y})^2\) \(y\)
  4. \(SS_{xx}=\sum_{i=1}^n(x_i-\bar{x})^2\) \(x\)
  5. \(SD_y^2=\frac{\sum_{i=1}(y_i-\bar{y})^2}{n-1}=\frac{SS_{yy}}{n-1}\) \(y\)
  6. \(SD_x^2=\frac{\sum_{i=1}(x_i-\bar{x})^2}{n-1}=\frac{SS_{xx}}{n-1}\) \(x\)
  7. \(S_{xy}=\sum_{i=1}^n(x_i-\bar{x})(y_i-\bar{y})\)\(x,y\)
  8. \(CV_{xy}=\frac{\sum_{i=1}^n(x_i-\bar{x})(y_i-\bar{y})}{n-1}=\frac{S_{xy}}{n-1}\)
  9. \(r_{xy}=\frac{CV_{xy}}{SD_xSD_y}\)\(x,y\)
  10. \(SS_{RES}=\sum_{i=1}^n\hat\varepsilon^2=\sum_{i=1}^n(y_i-\hat\alpha-\hat\beta x_i)^2\)

OLS

  1. \((\bar{x},\bar{y})\)

@ref(eq:hatalpha) @ref(eq:hatbeta)

\[ \begin{aligned} \hat\alpha &= \bar{y} - \hat\beta\bar{x} \\ \hat y_i &= \hat\alpha + \hat\beta x_i \\ \Rightarrow \hat y_i &= \bar{y}+\hat\beta(x_i-\bar{x}) \end{aligned} (\#eq:lmcenter) \]

\(\hat x_i=\bar{x}\) \(\hat y_i=\bar{y}\)

  1. \(\hat\alpha,\hat\beta,\hat\sigma^2\)
  2. \(\hat\alpha, \hat\beta\) \(\hat\sigma^2\) MLE
  3. \(\hat\alpha, \hat\beta\) \(\alpha, \beta\)

\(\hat\beta\)

\[ \begin{equation} \hat\beta=\frac{S_{xy}}{SS_{xx}}=\frac{CV_{xy}}{SD_x^2} \end{equation} (\#eq:hatbetaalt) \]

\(Y\) \(X\) \(X\) \(Y\)

\(\hat\beta_{y|x}\) \(x\) \(y\)

\[ \begin{equation} \hat\beta_{y|x} = \frac{CV_{xy}}{SD_x^2} \text{ and } \hat\beta_{x|y} = \frac{CV_{xy}}{SD_y^2} \\ \text{Hence, } \hat\beta_{y|x}\hat\beta_{x|y} = r^2_{xy} \end{equation} (\#eq:r2) \]

Pearson

Pearson (Section @ref(randbeta))

\(r^2\)

Pearson

\[ \begin{equation} r^2 = \frac{SS_{yy}-SS_{RES}}{SS_{yy}} = 1-\frac{SS_{RES}}{SS_{yy}} \end{equation} (\#eq:rSSyySSres) \]

\[ \frac{SS_{RES}}{SS_{yy}} = \frac{\sum_{i=1}^n(y_i-\hat\alpha-\hat\beta x_i)^2}{\sum_{i=1}^n(y_i-\bar{y})^2} \]

@ref(eq:hatalpha) : \(\hat\alpha=\bar{y}-\hat{\beta}\bar{x}\)

\[ \begin{aligned} \frac{SS_{RES}}{SS_{yy}} &= \frac{\sum_{i=1}^n[(y_i-\bar{y})-\hat\beta(x_i-\bar{x})]^2}{\sum_{i=1}^n(y_i-\bar{y})^2} \\ &=\frac{\sum_{i=1}^n(y_i-\bar{y})^2}{\sum_{i=1}^n(y_i-\bar{y})^2}-\frac{2\hat\beta\sum_{i=1}^n(x_i-\bar{x})(y_i-\bar{y})}{\sum_{i=1}^n(y_i-\bar{y})^2}+\frac{\hat\beta^2\sum_{i=1}^n(x_i-\bar{x})^2}{\sum_{i=1}^n(y_i-\bar{y})^2}\\ &=1-\frac{2\hat\beta S_{xy}}{SS_{yy}} + \frac{\hat\beta^2SS_{xx}}{SS_{yy}} \end{aligned} \]

\(\hat\beta=\frac{\sum_{i=1}^n(x_i-\bar{x})(y_i-\bar{y})}{\sum_{i=1}^n(x_i-\bar{x})^2}=\frac{S_{xy}}{SS_{xx}}, r^2=\frac{S_{xy}^2}{SS_{xx}SS_{yy}}\)

\[ \begin{aligned} \frac{SS_{RES}}{SS_{yy}} &= 1-\frac{2S_{xy}^2}{SS_{yy}SS_{xx}}+\frac{S_{xy}^2}{SS_{xx}SS_{yy}}\\ &=1-2r^2+r^2\\ &=1-r^2\\ \Rightarrow r^2&=1-\frac{SS_{RES}}{SS_{yy}} \end{aligned} \]

Pearson \(r^2\) \(SS_{yy}\) \(1-SS_{RES}\) \(R^2\) (Section @ref(Rsquare))

Pearson \(t\)

\[ \begin{equation} t=r\sqrt{\frac{n-2}{1-r^2}} \end{equation} (\#eq:t-r2) \]

\(r^2\) @ref(eq:rSSyySSres) \(r^2=\frac{S_{xy}^2}{SS_{xx}SS_{yy}}\)

\[ \begin{aligned} \frac{r^2}{1-r^2} & = \frac{\frac{S_{xy}^2}{SS_{xx}SS_{yy}}}{\frac{SS_{RES}}{SS_{yy}}} \\ & = \frac{S_{xy}^2}{SS_{xx}SS_{RES}} \\ & = \frac{S_{xy}^2}{SS_{xx}(n-2)\hat\sigma^2} \end{aligned} \]

@ref(eq:varhatbeta) \(\hat\sigma^2=V(\hat\beta)SS_{xx}\)

\[ \begin{aligned} \frac{r^2}{1-r^2} & = \frac{S_{xy}^2}{SS^2_{xx}(n-2)V(\hat\beta)} \\ & = \frac{\hat\beta^2}{(n-2)V(\hat\beta)} \\ \Rightarrow t=r\sqrt{\frac{n-2}{1-r^2}} \end{aligned} \]

\[ SS_{RES} = \sum_{i=1}^n \hat\varepsilon^2= \sum_{i=1}^n(y_i-\hat y_i)^2 \]

(Section @ref(meanfunction)) \(E(Y|X=x) = \alpha+\beta x\) \(\alpha, \beta\) \(\sigma^2\) @ref(eq:hatalpha) @ref(eq:hatbeta) @ref(eq:sigma2right)

\(E(Y|X=x)=\alpha\)

\[ SS_{RES} = \sum_{i=1}^n(y_i-\hat\alpha)^2 \]

@ref(eq:hatalpha) \(\hat\alpha=\bar{y}-\hat\beta\) \(\hat\alpha = \bar{y}\)

\[ SS_{RES} = \sum_{i=1}^n(y_i-\bar{y})^2 =SS_{yy} \]

ANOVA () \((SS_{RES_{NULL}})\)

  1. \((SS_{REG})\)
  2. \((SS_{RES_{ALT}})\)

\[ \begin{equation} \sum_{i=1}^n(y_i-\bar{y})^2 = \sum_{i=1}^n(\hat{y}-\bar{y})^2 + \sum_{i=1}^n(y_i-\hat{y}_i)^2 \\ SS_{RES_{NULL}}(SS_{yy}) = SS_{REG} + SS_{RES_{ALT}} \end{equation} (\#eq:SSres-partition) \]

\[ \begin{aligned} \sum_{i=1}^n(y_i-\bar{y})^2 &= \sum_{i=1}^n[(\hat{y}-\bar{y})+(y_i-\hat{y})]^2\\ &= \sum_{i=1}^n(\hat{y}-\bar{y})^2+\sum_{i=1}^n(y_i-\hat{y})^2+2\sum_{i=1}^n(\hat{y}_i-\bar{y})(y_i-\hat{y}) \\ &= SS_{REG} + SS_{RES_{ALT}} + 2\sum_{i=1}^n(\hat{y}_i-\bar{y})(y_i-\hat{y}) \end{aligned} \]

\(\sum_{i=1}^n(\hat{y}_i-\bar{y})(y_i-\hat{y})=0\)

@ref(eq:lmcenter) \(\hat{y}_i=\bar{y}+\hat{\beta}(x_i-\bar{x})\)

\[ \begin{aligned} \sum_{i=1}^n(\hat{y}_i-\bar{y})(y_i-\hat{y}) &= \sum_{i=1}^n(\bar{y}+\hat\beta(x_i-\bar{x})-\bar{y})(y_i-\bar{y}-\hat\beta(x_i-\bar{x})) \\ &= \sum_{i=1}^n\hat\beta(x_i-\bar{x})[y_i-\bar{y}-\hat\beta(x_i-\bar{x})] \\ &= \hat\beta\sum_{i=1}^n(x_i-\bar{x})(y_i-\bar{y}) - \hat\beta^2\sum_{i=1}^n(x_i-\bar{x}) \\ &= \frac{S_{xy}}{S_{xx}}S_{xy} - (\frac{S_{xy}}{S_{xx}})^2SS_{xx}\\ &= 0 \\ \Rightarrow SS_{RES_{NULL}}(SS_{yy}) &= SS_{REG} + SS_{RES_{ALT}} \end{aligned} \]

\(R^2\) coefficient of determination

@ref(eq:SSres-partition) \(SS_{REG}\) \(SS_{RES_{ALT}}\) \(\frac{SS_{REG}}{SS_{yy}}\) \(R^2\)

(Section @ref(rsquare))

\[ \begin{equation} R^2 = \frac{SS_{REG}}{SS_{yy}} = \frac{\sum_{i=1}^n(\hat{y}_i-\bar{y})^2}{\sum_{i=1}^n(y_i-\bar{y})^2} = 1-\frac{\sum_{i=1}^n(y_i-\hat{y}_i)^2}{\sum_{i=1}^n(y_i-\bar{y})^2} \end{equation} (\#eq:R-square) \]

\[ \begin{aligned} \text{Because } \mathbf{Y} & = \mathbf{X\hat\beta + \varepsilon} \\ \Rightarrow \mathbf{\varepsilon} & = \mathbf{Y - X\hat\beta}\\ \Rightarrow \mathbf{SS_{RES}} & = \varepsilon_1\times \varepsilon_1 + \varepsilon_2\times \varepsilon_2 + \cdots + \varepsilon_n\times \varepsilon_n \\ & = (\varepsilon_1, \varepsilon_2, \cdots, \varepsilon_n)\left( \begin{array}{c} \varepsilon_1\\ \varepsilon_2\\ \vdots\\ \varepsilon_n \end{array} \right) \\ & = \mathbf{\varepsilon^\prime} \mathbf{\varepsilon} \\ & = \mathbf{(Y-X\hat\beta)^\prime(Y-X\hat\beta)} \\ & = \mathbf{Y^\prime Y - X^\prime\hat\beta^\prime Y - Y^\prime X\hat\beta + X^\prime\hat\beta^\prime X \hat\beta} \\ \text{Because} &\text{ transpose of a scalar is a scalar:} \\ \mathbf{Y^\prime X\hat\beta} & = \mathbf{(Y^\prime X\hat\beta)^\prime = X^\prime\hat\beta^\prime Y} \\ \Rightarrow \mathbf{SS_{RES}} & = \mathbf{Y^\prime Y - 2X^\prime\hat\beta^\prime Y + X^\prime\hat\beta^\prime X \hat\beta}\\ \Rightarrow \mathbf{\frac{\partial SS_{RES}}{\partial \hat\beta}} & = \mathbf{-2X^\prime Y + 2 X^\prime X \hat\beta} = 0 \\ \Rightarrow \mathbf{\hat\beta} & = \mathbf{(X^\prime X)^{-1}X^\prime Y} \end{aligned} (\#eq:lm5-4) \]

Leverage

\[ \begin{aligned} l_i = \frac{1}{n} + \frac{x_i-\bar{x}}{SS_{xx}} \end{aligned} (\#eq:lm6-4) \]

\(\frac{1}{n}, 1\) \(1\)

(2018-05-14 2014 Paper 2-Q2 )

@ref(eq:lm5-7) \(\mathbf{P}\)

\[ \begin{aligned} & l_i = \mathbf{P}_{ii} \text{ The } i\text{ th diagonal element of } \\ & \mathbf{X(X^\prime X)^{-1}X^\prime} \end{aligned} (\#eq:lm6-5) \]

In multiple regression, leverage measures distance from the centre of the joint distribution of the predecitor variables, but with distance scaled by the directional degree of dispersion. Notice that the point with largest leverage would not have particularly high leverage in either simple linear regression models including only one of the two (or more) predictor variables. Further this point would not be readily identified in plots of each of the predictor variables against the dependent variable. The value of measures such as the leverage is greatest in complex multiple regression models where it can be difficult to identify points with an atypical () combination of predictor variables using more simple graphical techniques.
